<t>CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  age INT
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  duration INTERVAL
);

  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  muscle_group VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

  date DATE NOT NULL,
  sets INT,

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,

    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,

    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><s>create table example_table1 (
    column1 datatype primary key,
    column2 datatype not null,
    column3 datatype,
    column4 datatype
);</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);</t><s>create table example_table1 (
    column1 datatype primary key,
    column2 datatype not null,
    column3 datatype,
    column4 datatype
);</s>

    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);</t><s>CREATE TABLE example_table2 (
    column1 datatype PRIMARY KEY,
    column2 datatype NOT NULL,
    column3 datatype NOT NULL,
    column4 datatype,
    column5 datatype NOT NULL
);</s>

    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,

    age INT,

    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,

    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,

    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><s>create table example_table3 (
    column1 datatype primary key,
    column2 datatype not null,
    column3 datatype,
    column4 datatype,
    column5 datatype not null,
    column6 datatype
);</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,

    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL

<t>CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
